    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> parsnip[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped carrot</strong> and <strong>chopped parsnip</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has begun to soften, add your <strong>mince </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go, once browned, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your <strong>tomato paste<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>pie filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince mixture thickens, return the <strong>drained potatoes & veg </strong>to a low heat with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>root veg mash</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pie filling</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> root veg mash </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>root veg mash topped</strong> <strong>cottage pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the pie is nearly ready, wash your <strong>spring greens</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper then rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, and layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite \u2013 these are your <strong>garlicky greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/root-veg-mash-topped-lean-cottage-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>root veg mash topped</strong> <strong>cottage pie</strong> with the <strong>garlicky greens </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
